// Format of flags file is
// <FLAG|OPTION> FLAG-NAME (DEFAULT-VALUE?)
// ARG FOR <OPTION_NAME> <ARG_NAME> TYPE <[STR, INT, UINT, BOOL, CHAR]> <FROM [a, b, c]>?

FLAG EXPR-DBG false
FLAG VEXPR-DBG false
FLAG TOK-OUT true
FLAG VTOK-OUT false
FLAG VLTOK-OUT false
FLAG AST-OUT false
FLAG FLAGS-OUT true
FLAG SCOPE-OUT false
FLAG HADRON-VERIFY false

OPTION O

OPTION OUT
ARG FOR OUT OUTPUT TYPE STR FROM TOK, VTOK, VLTOK, AST, FLAGS, SCOPE

OPTION E
ARG FOR E Entry TYPE STR

OPTION DEBUGLVL
ARG FOR DEBUGLVL LVL TYPE UINT FROM 0, 1, 2